job_history.work_description: Responsible for preparing and posting entries for the daily posting packet. Verifies and balances system originated interfaces and posts non-system generated transactions prepared from other sources. A monitor flow of credit union transactions from the various supporting systems into and out of the general ledger daily, and identifies and resolves errors, omissions, and irregularities to provide accurate records for TFCU and its service organizations.

Coordinate and supervise employees within Accounts Payable interacting with internal customers and external suppliers monitoring all controls. Oversee employee business expense processing for multiple business units leading projects such as system testing and implementation.

Perform a variety of support duties related to the accounting function within the credit union; assisting the accounting team in maintaining the financial, statistical, and accounting records; Accounts Payable processing; posting general ledger entries; reconciling general ledger accounts as assigned and miscellaneous filing/scanning of checks, invoices and branch daily work.
Provided customers with prompt, accurate, courteous and professional banking service. Identified and referred sales opportunities to Relationship Bankers about products and services.

skills.name: General Accounting
skills.explanation: Over 8 years of experience in various accounting roles, including preparing and posting entries, verifying and balancing system interfaces, and reconciling general ledger accounts, indicating expert-level mastery.

skills.name: Financial Reconciliation
skills.explanation: Extensive experience in reconciling general ledger accounts and identifying and resolving errors, omissions, and irregularities, showing strong proficiency.

skills.name: Accounts Payable
skills.explanation: Significant experience in Accounts Payable processing, including supervising employees and monitoring controls, indicating strong proficiency.

skills.name: Leadership
skills.explanation: Experience in supervising employees and leading projects, such as system testing and implementation, showing a solid level of proficiency in leadership.

skills.name: Financial Analysis
skills.explanation: Experience in maintaining financial, statistical, and accounting records, and assisting the accounting team, indicating a solid working proficiency.

skills.name: Customer Service
skills.explanation: Experience in providing customers with prompt, accurate, courteous, and professional banking service, showing some practical experience.

skills.name: Sales
skills.explanation: Basic familiarity with identifying and referring sales opportunities to Relationship Bankers, but limited experience in this area.
